   "source": [
    "# Error Recovery in Agents\n",
    "\n",
    "Learning objectives:\n",
    "- Classify errors (transient, permanent, semantic)\n",
    "- Implement retry with exponential backoff\n",
    "- Design fallback strategies\n",
    "- Validate LLM outputs before using\n",
    "- Use circuit breakers to prevent cascading failures\n",
    "\n",
    "**Prerequisites:** Python 3.8+, anthropic SDK"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import time\n",
    "import json\n",
    "from datetime import datetime, timedelta\n",
    "from enum import Enum\n",
    "from typing import Optional, Any, Callable, List\n",
    "from anthropic import Anthropic\n",
    "\n",
    "client = Anthropic()\n",
    "print(\"✓ Setup ready: error recovery libraries\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Level 1: Retry with Exponential Backoff"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def classify_error(error_msg: str) -> str:\n",
    "    \"\"\"Classify error as transient, permanent, or semantic\"\"\"\n",
    "    msg = error_msg.lower()\n",
    "    if any(x in msg for x in [\"timeout\", \"rate limit\", \"503\", \"502\", \"connection\"]):\n",
    "        return \"transient\"\n",
    "    elif any(x in msg for x in [\"400\", \"404\", \"401\", \"not found\"]):\n",
    "        return \"permanent\"\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        return \"semantic\"\n",
    "\n",
    "def call_with_retry(func: Callable, max_retries: int = 3) -> Optional[Any]:\n",
    "    \"\"\"Call with exponential backoff\"\"\"\n",
    "    backoff = 1\n",
    "    for attempt in range(1, max_retries + 1):\n",
    "        try:\n",
    "            return func()\n",
    "        except Exception as e:\n",
    "            error_type = classify_error(str(e))\n",
    "            if error_type == \"permanent\":\n",
    "                print(f\"Permanent error, not retrying: {e}\")\n",
    "                return None\n",
    "            if attempt < max_retries:\n",
    "                print(f\"Attempt {attempt}: {error_type} error. Retrying in {backoff}s...\")\n",
    "                time.sleep(backoff)\n",
    "                backoff *= 2\n",
    "            else:\n",
    "                print(f\"Max retries exhausted\")\n",
    "                return None\n",
    "\n",
    "# Test\ndef flaky_function():\n",
    "    import random\n",
    "    if random.random() < 0.7:\n",
    "        raise TimeoutError(\"Timeout\")\n",
    "    return \"Success\"\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Testing retry logic:\")\n",
    "result = call_with_retry(flaky_function, max_retries=3)\n",
    "print(f\"Result: {result}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Level 2: Validation and Self-Correction"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "class ValidatingLLMAgent:\n    \"\"\"Validate LLM outputs and ask for correction\"\"\"\n    \n    def __init__(self, client):\n        self.client = client\n        self.max_corrections = 2\n    \n    def validate_json(self, text: str) -> tuple[bool, Optional[dict], str]:\n        try:\n            data = json.loads(text)\n            return True, data, \"\"\n        except json.JSONDecodeError as e:\n            return False, None, f\"Invalid JSON: {str(e)[:100]}\"\n    \n    def query_with_validation(self, prompt: str, validate_type: str = \"json\") -> Optional[Any]:\n        messages = [{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": prompt}]\n        \n        for attempt in range(1, self.max_corrections + 1):\n            response = self.client.messages.create(\n                model=\"claude-3-5-sonnet-20241022\",\n                max_tokens=200,\n                messages=messages\n            )\n            \n            output = response.content[0].text\n            \n            if validate_type == \"json\":\n                is_valid, data, error = self.validate_json(output)\n                if is_valid:\n                    print(f\"✓ Valid JSON on attempt {attempt}\")\n                    return data\n            else:\n                return output\n            \n            if attempt < self.max_corrections:\n                print(f\"✗ Invalid {validate_type} on attempt {attempt}: {error}\")\n                messages.append({\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": output})\n                messages.append({\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": f\"Invalid output. Error: {error}. Please fix it.\"})\n            else:\n                print(f\"✗ Max corrections exhausted\")\n                return None\n\n# Test\nagent = ValidatingLLMAgent(client)\nresult = agent.query_with_validation(\n    'Generate JSON with keys \"name\" and \"age\". Output only valid JSON.',\n    validate_type=\"json\"\n)\nprint(f\"Final result: {result}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Level 3: Circuit Breaker Pattern"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "class CircuitState(Enum):\n    CLOSED = \"closed\"\n    OPEN = \"open\"\n    HALF_OPEN = \"half_open\"\n\n",
    "class CircuitBreaker:\n    \"\"\"Prevent hammering of failing services\"\"\"\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def __init__(self, failure_threshold: int = 5, recovery_timeout: int = 30):\n",
    "        self.state = CircuitState.CLOSED\n",
    "        self.failure_count = 0\n",
    "        self.failure_threshold = failure_threshold\n",
    "        self.recovery_timeout = recovery_timeout\n",
    "        self.last_failure = None\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def record_success(self):\n",
    "        self.failure_count = 0\n",
    "        self.state = CircuitState.CLOSED\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def record_failure(self):\n",
    "        self.failure_count += 1\n",
    "        self.last_failure = datetime.now()\n",
    "        if self.failure_count >= self.failure_threshold:\n",
    "            self.state = CircuitState.OPEN\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def can_call(self) -> bool:\n",
    "        if self.state == CircuitState.CLOSED:\n",
    "            return True\n",
    "        elif self.state == CircuitState.OPEN:\n",
    "            if datetime.now() > self.last_failure + timedelta(seconds=self.recovery_timeout):\n",
    "                self.state = CircuitState.HALF_OPEN\n",
    "                self.failure_count = 0\n",
    "                return True\n",
    "            return False\n",
    "        return True\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def status(self) -> str:\n",
    "        return f\"{self.state.value} ({self.failure_count} failures)\"\n",
    "\n",
    "# Test\nbreaker = CircuitBreaker(failure_threshold=3, recovery_timeout=5)\n",
    "\nprint(\"Simulating failures:\")\n",
    "for i in range(10):\n",
    "    if breaker.can_call():\n",
    "        if i < 3:  # Fail first 3\n",
    "            breaker.record_failure()\n",
    "            print(f\"  Attempt {i+1}: FAIL - Circuit: {breaker.status()}\")\n",
    "        else:\n",
    "            breaker.record_success()\n",
    "            print(f\"  Attempt {i+1}: SUCCESS - Circuit: {breaker.status()}\")\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        print(f\"  Attempt {i+1}: SKIPPED - Circuit OPEN\")\n",
    "    time.sleep(0.5)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Key Takeaways\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Classify errors correctly** — Transient (retry), permanent (don't), semantic (validate/clarify)\n",
    "2. **Exponential backoff** — 1s, 2s, 4s, 8s prevents hammering recovering services\n",
    "3. **Validate before using** — Never trust LLM output without validation\n",
    "4. **Fallback strategies** — Primary tool → fallback tool → simplified approach\n",
    "5. **Circuit breakers** — Stop retrying unhealthy services; check recovery periodically\n",
    "6. **Log everything** — Error type, retry count, final outcome. Data drives improvements.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Related:** Observability, Latency Optimization, Agent Monitoring"
   ]
  }
